node.accessibility_caption: Photo by JJ_MOBILEPHOTOGRAPHY in Saguaro National Park-Tucson Mountain District with @allophile_. May be an image of nature.

node.text:
Hello everyone! It’s Dee again to share my final feature of the night with you!😊 🙋🏻‍♀️
.
.
There’s nothing dry and dusty about this desert sunset shot by Joe @allophile_ , is there?? 😍 🏜
The Saguaro cactus silhouettes make a striking centerpiece against the amazing array of colors of what Joe identified as “the monsoon skies”. 
Of course, I had to look that up, 🤓 and below is what I found: 

“For a few months each year, the Desert Southwest transforms into a storm photographer’s paradise. Nourishing rains pour from the sky in daily deluges. Hulking thunderheads tap the desert heat to soar higher than jetliners fly. Bolts of electricity light up the sky as bursts of wind descend to the ground, kicking up vast clouds of dust…..
Strictly speaking, a monsoon is a seasonal wind shift, but when it arrives, it’s like flipping a switch. The ordinarily arid desert landscape quickly becomes a minefield of thunderstorms….” ⛈ 🏜 
.
.
“Like flipping a switch….” I love that description 🤩 and can certainly see why this time of year “lights” Joe’s photography energy  up in a BIG way!! 💫 📱 
.
Please take a moment to visit Joe’s “electric” gallery @allophile_ and share lots of warm JJMP love  while you’re there!!!! 😊🧡💙
.
.
I look forward to seeing you next week!😃🙋🏻‍♀️ Dee (@iheart_alfresco_photos) 
.
.
Featured: @allophile_ 
Tag: #jj_mp_allophile_ 
Location: Tucson, Arizona 
Device: iPhone 
.
.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by JJ_MOBILEPHOTOGRAPHY in Hudson River Waterfront Walkway with @apeaseye. May be an image of body of water.

node.text:
“Attention, JJMP shoppers”🙋🏻‍♀️ 
It’s Dee here and I hope you are having an extra special day today!! 🤗 🤍🙏🏼 
.
.
💙💡 This Blue light special that Allison @apeaseye captured and tagged to our DOF weeklong challenge (@jj_mobilephoto_dof ) caught my eye and helped get me out of the early morning fog I was still in while scrolling. 🌫 👌 (Maybe I also need more of that delicious coffee or tea from our last 2 dof challenge features. 😅☕️👍)
.
.
This appealing shot has many features going for it, besides the successful shallow-to-medium DOF that Allison achieved. 
I love the leading line of the curved railing, and the BNW-but-not look that this foggy morning  on the Hudson River creates. 
.
This wet, watery shot is also a good opportunity to remember our fellow JJMP friends and family in NYC and surrounding areas that suffered such devastating flooding and loss last week due to tropical storm Ida.😢❤️😙
*
*
💡And on a lighter note, I would also REALLY love to see a show of 🤚’s below, for any of you, especially those outside of the USA, that know or still use the term “blue light special.” I’m very curious if it transcended beyond 🇺🇸 or ⏰. 🤓😘💙
.
.
After that, Please take some time to visit Allison’s wonderful gallery @apeaseye and spread lots of JJMP love and light while you’re there too!💙🤍

I’ll be back to share one more  feature with you this evening!! 😃🙋🏻‍♀️ Dee @iheart_alfresco_photos
.
.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by JJ_MOBILEPHOTOGRAPHY on September 03, 2021. May be an image of nature and grass.

node.text:
D.O.F. (Depth of Field) 
👉👉Swipe through the pics
.
😃👋 It’s Kel @mackelleen here!
Before using Instagram, I never heard of the term D.O.F.and I was confused by it for quite a while. 🤔
Sometimes, it’s used casually, which can cause more confusion.🤷🏼‍♀️

‼️Don’t forget to tag your mobile images that demonstrate DOF, for our Weeklong Challenge!!!‼️
👀See our post from this morning! (Friday Sept 3)
.
🤚🚫1st - what it’s NOT (sorry!):
Technically, Depth of Field is NOT about how close the in-focus object is to the lens.
(When using a cellphone, this does impact the DOF, but it’s not what defines it.)
💎Rather, it is the depth of the scene that is in focus.
.
1️⃣👉 🍞Think of the image as slices of bread in a loaf, and you are a little creature eating through it, heel to heel! 🐭🍞
‼️But the 🐭 is only allowed to eat the slices that are in focus! 🔎🤔
...
👉In this image, the slices of “bread” are:
☘️🌱first slice is clover/grass
➿then a feather
🌱more🌱, more🌱, more🌱,
🚙🚐vehicles
and eventually,
⛅️🌅the clouds/sunset is the last piece of bread.
.
❗️Most cellphones will automatically shoot DEEP depth of field - attempting to get everything in focus.❗️
.
👉Swipe to next “page” in this post😉

Let’s compare the two sides on this image....
2️⃣🔹👉On the LEFT side, with deep DOF, you can see MANY slices in focus. (Grass🌱 grass🌱 grass🌱 vehicles🚐🚙, and the sunset🌅!)
.
The 🐭 would eat MANY slices of bread! This is DEEP depth of field.
.
3️⃣🔸👉On the RIGHT side, with shallow DOF, you only see one slice in focus, really! (The feather➿ and a tiny bit of 🌱 under it.)
.
The 🐭 would only eat one piece of bread, right? This is SHALLOW depth of field.
.
👉Swipe to 4th page!

4️⃣ I have included another photo #4, which shows a medium depth of field.
🔺Notice on the fourth photo, the feather ➿is not in focus, and neither are the vehicles🚙🚐/ sunset🌅.
👉The only part in focus is the 🌱🌱🌱 between the feather and the vehicles.
So, not deep, and not shallow - MEDIUM depth of field (D.O.F.).🤔
.
We can’t wait to see your posts for this weeklong challenge!!! 😃🎉

Check out the prior post for challenge rules!! ‼️

Hello and Happy “Challenge Announcement” Day, Fam! 🥳 🎊 

We have a very special WEEKLONG CHALLENGE that begins today. 
Our weeklong challenges are hosted by our own jj_mp team. Our mods will be selecting at least 1 winning submission to feature from the challenge tag each day. 🎉🎉🎉
You can tag to the challenge all week! The challenge closes on Thursday, September 9th at 9pm Eastern time.❗️
.
👉👉Check out our next post today, if the idea of Depth of Field (DOF) is a little fuzzy! 😃
.
.
Theme: “Depth of Field”
#jj_mp_iheart_alfresco_photos 
.
‼️Challenge Rules:‼️
▶️ MUST be following @jj_mobilephotography
▶️ Specify which mobile device you used

▶️ Tag #jj_mobilephoto_dof

▶️New or old photos okay (we encourage new ones so get out there and shoot!)
▶️No previously featured (here on jj_mp) photos please
▶️ Don't forget to 1,2,3: For every 1 picture you post, comment on 2 others in the tag, and like 3 others.  This is also about building community and connecting with others.
